Module Getopt:
These functions are available with the following lines of code:

#include <mudlib.h>
inherit M_GETOPT;


argument_explode(arg) --  assumes the arg passed is the
	argument to some unix-like command where args are space seperated
	unless enclosed in non-escaped quotes.  Returns an array of the args.

getopt(args, options) --  Takes an array (args) and parses
	flags out of it.  Returns an array, the first element 
	being a mapping of flag : value, the second an array of the remaining
	args with the flag information removed.
	Options should be a string of single character flags the command accepts,
	followed by a colon (:) if the flag will take an argument.

parse_argument(input, options) -- calls argument_explode() and then getopt().
	Returns the value of getopt()
